%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestvalidation/OrderRequest.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}



*Automatic rejection — <<<@Validated>>> + <<<@Valid>>>

  Placing <<<@Validated>>> on the service class and <<<@Valid>>> on the <<<@RequestBody>>> parameter
  is all that is required.  When a request fails validation, OfficeFloor returns <<<400 Bad Request>>>
  before the method body is entered — the service method is never called for an invalid request:

%{snippet|file=${basedir}/src/main/resources/officefloor/rest/order.POST.yml|ignoreDownloadError=false}

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestvalidation/PlaceOrderService.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}

  This is identical to how <<<@Validated>>> works on a Spring <<<@RestController>>> — OfficeFloor
  delegates to Spring's validation infrastructure without any additional configuration.



*Manual error handling — <<<BindingResult>>>

  When the service method needs to inspect validation errors itself — for example to return a
  structured error body — declare a <<<BindingResult>>> parameter immediately after the
  <<<@Valid>>>-annotated parameter.  OfficeFloor passes validation errors through <<<BindingResult>>>
  and the method body always executes, even when there are errors:

%{snippet|file=${basedir}/src/main/resources/officefloor/rest/order/binding.POST.yml|ignoreDownloadError=false}

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestvalidation/PlaceOrderBindingService.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}

  The <<<BindingResult>>> parameter must immediately follow the <<<@Valid>>>-annotated parameter,
  exactly as required in Spring MVC.



